ITEC alumni recently converged at India House for a day that celebrates Indian Technical and Economic Cooperation. The chief guest was Foreign Affairs CAS Ababu Namwamba. Gideon Mwendwa and Dr Daniel Otwoma, two ITEC alumni, shared their experiences of training in India. Indian High Commissioner Rahul Chabbra handed a prize to Pravin Eazhawa, winner of the Gandhi online quiz held on the occasion of the 150th birth anniversary of Mahatma Gandhi. Leaders present included Education TVET PS Kevit Desai, Kisumu Governor Anyang Nyongâ€™o and Narok Governor Samuel Tunai.